caseText:"<p>XYZ Ltd., a publicly listed company based in India, is in the process of appointing a new independent director to comply with Section 149 of the Companies Act, 2013. This section mandates that a certain number of directors must be independent, particularly for listed companies. The appointment process involves the board&rsquo;s evaluation of potential candidates, ensuring that they meet the criteria for independence as outlined in the Act</p> <p>The current board members are:</p> <ul> <li>Mr. Ashok Patil (Chairman)</li> <li>Ms. Sunita Rao (Managing Director)</li> <li>Mr. Rakesh Mehra (Non-Executive Director)</li> <li>Ms. Kavita Desai (Independent Director)</li> <li>Mr. Vishal Bhatia (CFO)</li> </ul> <p>XYZ Ltd. needs to fill a vacancy created by the recent resignation of one of its independent directors, Mr. Ajay Singh.</p> <p>The board is considering following three candidates for the role of independent director:</p> <ol> <li>Mr. Anil Saxena</li> </ol> <ul> <li>Former CFO of a major tech firm.</li> <li>No material or pecuniary relationships with XYZ Ltd.</li> <li>Known for his integrity and financial expertise.</li> </ul> <p>2.&nbsp;Ms. Pooja Reddy</p> <ul> <li>Former CEO of a competitor company.</li> <li>Holds a significant amount of shares in XYZ Ltd.</li> <li>Has a strong background in corporate governance.</li> </ul> <p>3.&nbsp;Mr. Deepak Shah&nbsp;</p> <ul> <li>Retired partner from a major law firm.</li> <li>Provides occasional consulting services to XYZ Ltd.</li> <li>Experienced in regulatory compliance.</li> </ul> <p>Criteria for appointment of an Independent Director</p> <p>As per Section 149(6) of the Companies Act, 2013, an independent director must:</p> <ul> <li>Not have any pecuniary relationship with the company, its holding, subsidiary, or associate company, or their promoters, or directors during the two immediately preceding financial years or during the current financial year.</li> <li>Not be related to promoters or directors in the company.</li> <li>Not have any material relationship that could affect their independence.</li> </ul> <p><strong>Board Discussion </strong></p> <p>Mr. Ashok Patil highlights the importance of appointing an independent director who can provide unbiased oversight and has no conflicts of interest. Ms. Sunita Rao emphasizes the need for someone with strong financial acumen to help the board navigate the company&rsquo;s growth phase. Mr. Rakesh Mehra suggests prioritizing candidates who are familiar with industry regulations. Ms. Kavita Desai stresses the necessity of a candidate with a deep understanding of corporate governance.</p>",
